   Here is the the 58-42 roll call by which the
Senate failed Tuesday to garner the necessary two-thirds vote to
pass a constitutional amendment to outlaw flag desecration.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to amend the
Constitution and a ``no'' vote was a vote to leave it intact.
   Voting ``yes'' were 20 Democrats and 38 Republicans.
   Voting ''no'' were 35 Democrats and 7 Republicans.
